{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/blog/tera-saturday-1","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>And now for something completely different: <strong>TeraSaturday</strong>, a weekly update post about all the neat stuff that has been going on in\nthe world of Terasology! Half blog, half changelog, completely cool. Probably. I mean, there aren't any laser sharks...\nor laser raptors... or even laser eye surgery. But hopefully it will still meet your coolness expectations.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li>The biggest Terasology news this week is that it marks the end of this year's Google Code-In, and a big <em>thank you!</em>\ngoes out to everyone who participated, students and mentors alike! It's been great helping everyone experiment and learn\nover the past couple of months, and I certainly hope to see everyone more in the future.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"new-features-the-fun-stuff\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#new-features-the-fun-stuff\" aria-label=\"new features the fun stuff permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>New Features (The Fun Stuff)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>If you've been making new block shapes lately, you've probably become familiar with the challenges of our old Blender\nplugin. It's not compatible with the current version of Blender, it's tricky to install, and getting things to rotate\nproperly can be messy. Like making a banana smoothie without a lid. And so you'll probably be glad to hear that Pollend\nand I have released the first beta version of a brand new <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/BlenderAddon/releases/tag/v2.0.0-beta\">Blender Block Shape Plugin</a> for Blender 2.8. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 113.02083333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/3e828/blender_block_plugin.webp 192w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/e6f2f/blender_block_plugin.webp 384w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/8b983/blender_block_plugin.webp 768w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/385bc/blender_block_plugin.webp 810w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/8514f/blender_block_plugin.png 192w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/804b2/blender_block_plugin.png 384w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/e5715/blender_block_plugin.png 768w,\n/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/d7542/blender_block_plugin.png 810w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/1b9393c64fa62f690feaba045922dbeb/e5715/blender_block_plugin.png\"\n            alt=\"The plugin in action\"\n            title=\"The plugin in action\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>It can be installed normally from Blender's addon menu, it can import and export all the basic engine shapes without\ngetting confused about which way is up, and it is 100% laser-shark-free, guaranteed. There is no such guarantee about\nbugs, however. So if you spot one, make sure you jump on a table and scream at us to squish it. <em>(Or just <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/BlenderAddon/\">create an\nissue</a> in the GitHub repo. We're more likely to hear you that way.)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.3125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/3e828/grass_color.webp 192w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/e6f2f/grass_color.webp 384w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/8b983/grass_color.webp 768w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/0528c/grass_color.webp 1053w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/8514f/grass_color.png 192w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/804b2/grass_color.png 384w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/e5715/grass_color.png 768w,\n/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/34e70/grass_color.png 1053w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/22ee6af984dd1384960c92788ffb4101/e5715/grass_color.png\"\n            alt=\"Fancy trees and stuff\"\n            title=\"Fancy trees and stuff\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Leaves and grass have looked a little sad and dead since the BiomesAPI update last May removed block colorization.\nIt was an unfortunate side-effect of progress; since biomes were no longer part of the engine, the engine could not\nrely on the biome to tell it what colors the grass should be. But vibrant plants are sacrificed no more! They have\nreturned, relying upon the humidity and temperature directly instead of the biome.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 768px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.333333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/3e828/cotton.webp 192w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/e6f2f/cotton.webp 384w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/8b983/cotton.webp 768w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/e46b2/cotton.webp 960w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/8514f/cotton.png 192w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/804b2/cotton.png 384w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/e5715/cotton.png 768w,\n/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/d9199/cotton.png 960w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/e0ef50147f23c97b39e4b21ef57b5dce/e5715/cotton.png\"\n            alt=\"Cotton\"\n            title=\"Cotton\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>That is not the only way in which the basic flora has improved this week. <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/CoreAssets/commit/5e94cef5ef278a8dd7e93321689882493a97968d\">Cotton</a> textures in CoreAssets have been\nreplaced with brand new art from TheStygianHawk.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17286005/72514970-de110d80-389a-11ea-83c4-1376126fdfbb.png\" alt=\"An example of torches generated with askneller's work\" style=\"width:80%\">\n<ul>\n<li>New contributor askneller is working on better cave generation; as an intermediary step, world generating rasterizers\n(the systems that place the specific blocks) <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3825\">can depend on another rasterizer</a> which\nmust run first. This is important, because if you try to decorate your caves before you have any caves to decorate,\nyou're going to wind up with an empty cave and a visit from the Time Police for violating the laws of cause and effect. </li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"bugfixes-and-optimizations-the-nerdy-stuff\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#bugfixes-and-optimizations-the-nerdy-stuff\" aria-label=\"bugfixes and optimizations the nerdy stuff permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Bugfixes and Optimizations (The Nerdy Stuff)</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 683px; left:0; width: 100%;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/3e828/soap_mint.webp 192w,\n/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/e6f2f/soap_mint.webp 384w,\n/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/e2d2f/soap_mint.webp 683w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/8514f/soap_mint.png 192w,\n/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/804b2/soap_mint.png 384w,\n/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/bca35/soap_mint.png 683w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/bd4176bada66514c0c0eaf37054a25eb/bca35/soap_mint.png\"\n            alt=\"0 stars do not recommend these snacks\"\n            title=\"0 stars do not recommend these snacks\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Adrijaned has made improvements to the <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3589\">asset loading system</a>, including lots of\ndocumentation in an area that definitely needed more of it. Even for clever devs like <em>(ahem)</em> yours truly, figuring out\nhow to use code without any documentation is often bitter and confusing. Like those little soap-flavored mints on hotel\npillows. Always comment your code, kids. Don't make soap-flavored mints.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li>BenjaminAmos has done similar work over in the <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/Sensors/pull/4\">Sensors</a> module. So if you're into creating monsters that watch from\nthe shadows, or traps that activate when you step on them, or raptors that perform laser eye surgery when they see a\nshark, now you can proceed while knowing what you're doing. <em>(Knowing <strong>why</strong> you're doing it is something you'll have\nto figure out on your own. We can't help you there, sorry.)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li>DarkWeird has <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3804\">streamlined the chunk loading process</a> for worlds that have already been\ngenerated, which should be noticeably better at loading more of the world faster in multiplayer games when players are\nfar apart, or if you happen to be playing Terasology on a potato or a toaster. <em>(Unfortunately, we do not, at this time,\nsupport playing Terasology on toasted potatoes. Potato toasters, however, are fine.)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li>Pollend has <a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3821\">optimized the Discord Rich Presence integration</a>, which reduces Terasology's\noverall CPU usage by up to 2%. <em>(Note for future developers: increasing a counter to 5000 every millisecond instead of\njust waiting 5 seconds is... not fast. So don't do that. Please. Your CPU will thank you. Not literally, because that\nwould be creepy. It'll thank you in a non-verbal metaphorical way. By working faster. That is all.)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MovingBlocks/Terasology/pull/3823\">Windows XP users</a> might be able to play Terasology again, thanks to sladyn98. There's\njust one problem... none of us has a Windows XP system lying around anymore to fix it. <em>(Not even the people with potatoes\nand toasters.)</em> So if you or a loved one has been diagnosed with Microsoft Windows XP, you may be entitled to confirmation.\nPlease, try it out and let us know if it works.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>Thus concludes the first TeraSaturday changeblog. Hopefully, despite the absence of flashy lights and fierce creatures,\nyour thirst for coolness has been satiated. <em>(If not, I recommend a low-calorie sports drink.)</em> Enjoy the game, and I'll\nbe back for another update next week!</p>\n<!-- References -->","timeToRead":4,"excerpt":"And now for something completely different: TeraSaturday, a weekly update post about all the neat stuff that has been going on in\n the worldâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"TeraSaturday #1","ddate":"Jan 25th, 2020","tags":"TeraSaturday","author":"Jordan H. (Qwertygiy)","cover":{"publicURL":"/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/cover.jpg","childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/3e61c/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/7fcb3/cover.jpg 192w,\n/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/42594/cover.jpg 384w,\n/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/3e61c/cover.jpg 768w,\n/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/0a363/cover.jpg 1152w,\n/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/4b32a/cover.jpg 1536w,\n/static/86f27ac4c89ff64db1c2de4276891f00/74fd5/cover.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/tera-saturday-1","date":"2020-01-24T18:30:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/tera-saturday-1","category":null}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}